<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6457] LBHttpSolrServer: AIOOBE risk if counter overflows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6457</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.solr.client.solrj.impl.LBHttpSolrServer&lt;br/&gt;
line 442&lt;br/&gt;
      int count = counter.incrementAndGet();      &lt;br/&gt;
      ServerWrapper wrapper = serverList&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;count % serverList.length&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;when counter overflows, the mod operation of &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;count % serverList.length&quot; will start trying to use negative numbers as array indexes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;suggess to fixup it ,eg:&lt;br/&gt;
//keep count is greater than 0&lt;br/&gt;
int count = counter.incrementAndGet() &amp;amp; 0x7FFFFFF;  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
